 Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, which was reported to the WHO on 31 December 2019.<ref name=Elsevier>{{cite web |url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center |title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center |last=Elsevier |date= |website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Reynolds4March2020>{{Cite news |last=Reynolds |first=Matt |url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus |title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic? |date=4 March 2020 |work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020 |issn=1357-0978|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 has been much lower than [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]],<ref name=Imperial13March2020>{{cite web |url= https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/ |title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus |website=Imperial News|access-date=15 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Gov.ukHCIDDef>{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid |title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England |last= |first= |date= |website=GOV.UK |language=en|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=WFSA>{{cite web |url= https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus |title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus |last= |first= |date= |website=www.wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Imperial13March2020/>\n\n==Timeline==\n===March===\nOn 4 March, [[French Guiana]] had five confirmed cases of [[COVID-19]], all in [[Saint-Laurent du Maroni]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.antiguaobserver.com/five-coronavirus-cases-confirmed-in-french-guiana-march-4-2020/ |title=Five coronavirus cases confirmed in French Guiana March 4, 2020 |website=Antigua Observer |date=4 March 2020 |accessdate=5 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 6 March, [[Guiana Space Center]] has suspended launch activities. <ref name=\"arienespace\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.arianespace.com/press-release/covid-19-guiana-space-center-suspends-launch-campaigns/|title=COVID-19: Guiana Space Center suspends launch campaigns|website=Ariane Space|access-date=9 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 March, the following measure were announced by the [[Emmanuel Macron|President of the Republic]]: It is prohibited to leave the house except for essential journeys which includes: shopping for food, travelling to work, accessing healthcare, and exercising within 1 km of the household. <ref name=\"travel\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.guyane.gouv.fr/Politiques-publiques/Sante/Coronavirus-Covid-19/COVID-19-Informations/Mesures-de-restriction-de-circulation|title=Mesures de restriction de circulation |language=fr|website=guayne.gouv.fr|access-date=9 April 2020}}</ref> [[Marc Del Grande]], the [[List of colonial and departmental heads of French Guiana|Prefect]] of French Guiana, announced closing of borders with [[Suriname]] and [[Brazil]], mandatory 14 day quarantine for people coming from abroad, and a curfew between 21:00 and 05:00. <ref name=\"firstmeasures\">{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/guyane/cccc-822980.html|title=Coronavirus : un mois de confinement en Guyane en quelques dates...|language=fr|access-date=14 April 2020|website=Guyane la 1\u00e8re}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 March, all air travel for passengers will be halted from midnight onwards. <ref name=\"airport\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.franceguyane.fr/actualite/politique/les-deplacements-aeriens-en-outre-mer-officiellement-interdits-jusqu-au-15-avril-466935.php|title=Les d\u00e9placements a\u00e9riens en outre-mer officiellement interdits jusqu'au 15 avril|language=fr|website=France-Guyane|access-date=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 March, Marie-Laure Phinera-Horth, the Mayor of [[Cayenne]] had instituted a curfew from 20:00 to 05:00 unlike the rest of the region. <ref name=\"curfew\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.franceguyane.fr/actualite/politique/covid-19-il-faut-preparer-la-guyane-a-affronter-un-pic-important-466992.php|title=Covid-19: \"We must prepare Guyana to face an important peak\"|website=France-Guyane|language=fr|access-date=9 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 30 March, a member of the nursing staff at the Cayenne nursing home tested positive. <ref name=\"firstmeasures\"/>\n\n===April===\n\nOn 4 April, a laboratory assistant from Andr\u00e9e-Rosemon Hospital Center tested positive. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.franceguyane.fr/actualite/sante/coronavirus/covid-19-la-guyane-desormais-en-stade-2-de-l-epidemie-467153.php|title=Covid 19: Guiana is now in stage 2 of the epidemic|language=fr|website=France-Guyane|access-date=9 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 7 April, there were 77 cases and 34 recoveries. The districts affected are Saint-Laurent, [[Kourou]], [[Cayenne]] and [[Maripasoula]] <ref name=\"upd_04-07\">{{cite web|title=Covid Info du mardi 7 avril 2020|language=fr|url=http://www.guyane.gouv.fr/Politiques-publiques/Sante/Coronavirus-Covid-19/COVID-INFO/Covid-Info-du-mardi-7-avril-2020|website=www.guyane.gouv.fr|accessdate=8 April 2020}}</ref> Groupe Bernard Hayot has donated 1,300,000 masks for free to health works in [[Martinique]], [[Gaudeloupe]], Guiana, and [[R\u00e9union]] <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.franceguyane.fr/actualite/sante/coronavirus/le-groupe-bernard-hayot-fournit-1-3-million-de-masques-aux-soignants-467251.php|title=Groupe Bernard Hayot group donated 1.3 million masks to health workers (in French)|access-date=9 April 2020|website=France-Guyane}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 April, the [[European Union]] announced a grant of \u20ac8M (US$8.6M), which will be implemented by the [[Caribbean Public Health Agency]], for the fight against the Corona virus. French Guiana is one of the 24 members of the CARPHA. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.kaieteurnewsonline.com/2020/04/09/eu-provides-us8-6m-grant-for-cbean-to-combat-covid-19/|title=\nEU provides US$8.6M grant for C\u2019bean to combat COVID-19|website=Kaieteur News|access-date=9 April 2020}}</ref> \n<br>\nThe Agence r\u00e9gionale de sant\u00e9 Guyane released a special report on the situation: 780 tests had been performed, 985 contacts had been traced, 42 cases were imported and 41 cases resulted from [[community spread]]. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.guyane.ars.sante.fr/system/files/2020-04/Guyane_PER_COVID19_20200409_0.pdf|title=Point Epid\u00e9mio R\u00e9gional hebdomadaire \"Sp\u00e9cial COVID-19\" (PDF)|language=fr|website=guyane.ars.sante.fr|access-date=15 April 2020}}</ref>\n<br>\nA cluster of 13 cases has been located at the [[Indigenous peoples|indigenous]] village C\u00e9cilia in [[Matoury]]. 13 out of 16 suspected cases have tested positive. The Prefect has ordered a confinement of the village. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.franceguyane.fr/actualite/sante/coronavirus/13-cas-confirmes-dans-un-village-amerindien-a-matoury-467330.php|title=13 cases confirmed in an Amerindian in Matoury|language=fr|website=France-Guyane|access-date=10 April 2020}}</ref> On 14 April, six more children from C\u00e9cilia tested positive; they are getting better. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/guyane/coronavirus-15-avril-823386.html|title=Coronavirus : Un seul nouveau cas d\u00e9clar\u00e9 positif ce 15 avril en Guyane|website=Guyane la 1\u00e8re|language=fr|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 10 April, the report of the Scientific Council on the Evolution of the Coronavirus in the Overseas Territories has been released which calls for strict confinement, doubling of hospital capactity. <ref>{{cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/coronavirus-le-conseil-scientifique-craint-une-aggravation-de-la-situation-outre-mer-et-preconise-le-maintien-strict-du-confinement-821800.html|title=Coronavirus: the scientific council fears a worsening of the Overseas situation and recommends \"the strict maintenance of confinement\"|language=fr|access-date=12 April 2020|website=Guyane la 1\u00e8re}}</ref> ARS Guyane replied on 13 April that they will apply certain recommendations, but also stated that the number of ICU beds had been increased to 38 and is sufficient at moment given that there are currently no people on ICU. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/guyane/coronavirus-certaines-recommandations-du-conseil-scientifique-pour-l-outre-mer-seront-appliquees-en-guyane-822546.html|title=Coronavirus : certaines recommandations du conseil scientifique pour l\u2019outre-mer seront appliqu\u00e9es en Guyane|language=fr|access-date=14 April 2020|website=Guyane la 1\u00e8re}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Wailly_stele_4e_zouaves_inauguration_09.jpg|thumb|Marc Del Grande, Prefect of French-Guinea]]\nOn 11 April, France and [[Suriname]] announced joint efforts to prevent illegal crossings of the [[Maroni (river)|Maroni]] river separating Suriname and French Guiana, <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.waterkant.net/suriname/2020/04/11/maatregelen-suriname-en-frankrijk-bij-grens-ter-bestrijding-van-coronavirus/|title=Measures Suriname and France at border to prevent Coronavirus |language=nl|website=Waterkant|access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref> and established a contact point in [[Saint-Laurent-du-Maroni]] and [[Albina, Suriname|Albina]]. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.deboodschap.today/communique-de-presse-conjoint-entre-la-republique-du-suriname-et-la-republique-francaise-sur-les-actions-pour-controler-la-frontiere-dans-le-cadre-de-la-pandemie-covid-19-dans-le-bas/|title=Communiqu\u00e9 de presse conjoint entre  la R\u00e9publique du Suriname et la R\u00e9publique Fran\u00e7aise sur les actions  pour contr\u00f4ler la fronti\u00e8re dans le cadre de la pand\u00e9mie covid-19 dans  le bassin de maroni|language=fr|website=Nationaal Informatie Instituut De Boodschap|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref> On 13 April, the [[Marc Del Grande|Prefect]] mobilised the army to guard the river for its entire length. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.starnieuws.com/index.php/welcome/index/nieuwsitem/58105|title=French ambassador: Border of 520 kilometres is a challenge (in Dutch)|website=Star Nieuws|access-date=13 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 12 April, Dr. Hatem Kallel announced that the patient who had been in [[Intensive care unit|ICU]] since 2 April has been discharged. There are currently no patients in intensive care. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.franceguyane.fr/actualite/sante/coronavirus/covid-19-l-unique-patient-en-reanimation-est-sorti-aujourd-hui-467380.php|title=Covid-19 : l\u2019unique patient en r\u00e9animation est sorti aujourd\u2019hui|language=fr|website=France-Guyane|access-date=13 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 April, there are concerns about [[price gouging]], however Gilles Klaus, Director of [[Carrefour]] Matoury, denies the allegations. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.franceguyane.fr/actualite/economie-consommation/la-livraison-a-domicile-seduit-les-grandes-surfaces-467316.php|title=La livraison \u00e0 domicile s\u00e9duit les grandes surfaces|language=fr|website=France-Guyane|access-date=14 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 April, it was reported that following the outbreak in C\u00e9cilia, several indigenous villages mainly located in Matoury and [[Macouria]] have voluntarily locked down. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/guyane/centre-littoral/coronavirus-les-villages-amerindiens-de-l-ile-de-cayenne-se-mettent-volontairement-en-confinement-pour-mieux-se-proteger-823014.html|title=Coronavirus : Les villages am\u00e9rindiens de Macouria et Matoury se mettent volontairement en confinement pour mieux se prot\u00e9ger|website=Guyane la 1\u00e8re|language=fr|access-date=15 April 2020}}</ref>\n<br>\nOfficials from French Guiana's local authorities voted to set up an emergency fund of \u20ac 8.7 million in the form of 0-rate loans to help businesses. The opposition and tourism authority fear that it is not enough. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/guyane/coronavirus-les-conseillers-territoriaux-votent-le-fonds-d-urgence-economique-823324.html|title=Coronavirus : les conseillers territoriaux votent le Fonds d\u2019urgence \u00e9conomique |language=fr|website=Guyane la 1\u00e8re|access-date=15 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 April, it was announced that 330 healthcare worker at Andr\u00e9e Rosemon Hospital Center in Cayenne will be tested, because up to now five staff members have tested postive. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/guyane/centre-littoral/cayenne/coronavirus-823364.html|title=Coronavirus : 330 soignants et administratifs du Centre hospitalier Andr\u00e9e Rosemon vont \u00eatre test\u00e9s au Covid-19|language=fr|website=Guyane la 1\u00e8re|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Preventive measures==\n* All borders, airports, ports and space ports <ref name=\"arienespace\"/> are closed for passengers. <ref name=\"airport\"/>\n* All schools are closed. <ref name=\"bbc\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-51892477|title=Coronavirus: Spain and France announce sweeping restrictions|website=bbc|access-date=12 April 2020}}</ref>\n* A curfew has been instituted in Cayenne from 20:00 <ref name=\"curfew\"/> and 21:00 elsewhere. <ref name=\"firstmeasures\" />\n* Everybody should stay at home except for essential journeys. <ref name=\"travel\"/> Certificates are needed for exceptions. <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.guyane.gouv.fr/Politiques-publiques/Sante/Coronavirus-Covid-19/Attestations-derogatoires|title=Attestations d\u00e9rogatoires|language=fr,es,pt,en,srn|access-date=12 April 2020|website=guyane.gouv.fr}}</ref>\n* All non-essential businesses must close. <ref name=\"bbc\"/>\n\n==Crisis Management==\nFrench Guiana is an [[overseas department]] and [[Regions of France|region]] of the [[French Republic]] and the State is representated by a [[Prefect (France)|Prefect]]. One of the tasks of the Prefect is to manage major crises. [[Marc Del Grande]] is the current Prefect and therefore in charge of the management of the COVID-19 pandemic.\n\n==Statistics==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" align=\"left\"\n|+\n'''Number of cases chronologically'''\n!Date\n!Number of cases\n!Recovered\n!Dead\n|-\n|4-10 March\n|5\n|0\n|0\n|-\n|11-12 March\n|6 <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.guyane.ars.sante.fr/coronavirus-guyane-1-cas-secondaire-confirme-saint-laurent-du-maroni|title=Coronavirus Guyane : 1 cas \u00ab secondaire \u00bb confirm\u00e9 \u00e0 Saint-Laurent du Maroni|website=guyane.ars.sante.fr|accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref>\n|0\n|0\n|-\n|13-14 March\n|7 <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.guyane.ars.sante.fr/coronavirus-guyane-un-nouveau-cas-kourou-et-trois-patients-gueris|title=Coronavirus Guyane : Un nouveau cas \u00e0 Kourou et trois patients gu\u00e9ris|website=guyane.ars.sante.fr|accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref>\n|3\n|0\n|-\n|15-17 March\n|11<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.guyane.ars.sante.fr/coronavirus-guyane-4-nouveaux-cas-de-coronavirus-en-guyane|title=